    <div class="debate_points_list">
    <table class="sticky-enabled">
 <thead class="tableHeader-processed"><tr><th class="plus">Points For</th><th class="minus">Points Against</th> </tr></thead>
<tbody>
 <tr class="odd"><td class="for">We already recognize the benefits of individuals who are able to pay for their healthcare doing so.</td><td class="against">Allowing the sale of organs will harm state-financed health services and create a two-tier system</td> </tr>
 <tr class="even"><td class="for">Legalize the benefits of individuals who are able to pay for their healthcare doing so.</td><td class="against">Allowing the sale of organs will harm state-financed health services and create a two-tier systeising the sale of organs will eradicate the black market and ensure safer transplants.</td><td class="against">Allowing the sale of human organs in the First World will impact negatively on the Third World.</td> </tr>
 <tr class="odd"><td class="for">People should have rights over their own body and body parts.</td><td class="against">There are better solutions to the problems of organ shortages, such as the BMA system of ‘presumed consent’.</td> </tr>
 <tr class="even"><td class="for">The donor should be able to benefit financially, rather than being expected to donate organs with no reward.</td><td class="against">Individuals do not have an inviolable right of property over their organs.</td> </tr>
</tbody>
</table>
