?”<em> National Health Service. </em>http://www.uktransplant.org.uk/ukt/how_to_become_a_donor/living_kidney_donation/living_kidney_donation.jsp, accessed 20/08/11.</p><p><em>Blood and Transplant. </em>“Opt In or Opt Out.” <em>National Health Service.&nbsp; </em>http://www.uktransplant.org.uk/ukt/newsroom/statements_and_stances/statements/opt_in_or_out.jsp, accessed 21/08/11.</p><p><em>Blood and Transplant. </em>“Organ Donation.” <em>National Health Service. </em>http://www.uktransplant.org.uk/ukt/default.jsp, accessed 19/08/11.</p><p><em>Blood and Transplant. </em>“Survey shows huge support for organ donation.” <em>National Health Service. </em>March 25, 2003. <a href="http://www.organdonation.nhs.uk/ukt/newsroom/news_releases/article.jsp?releaseId=47" title="http://www.organdonation.nhs.uk/ukt/newsroom/news_releases/article.jsp?releaseId=47">http://www.organdonation.nhs.uk/ukt/newsroom/news_releases/article.jsp?r...</a>, accessed 21/08/11.</p><p><em>Business Wire. </em>“Americans Desperate for Organ Transplants Find the Black Market Can Be Deadly: Special Report in June Issue of Bloomberg Markets Magazine.” May 12, 2011. <a href="http://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20110512006179/en/Americans-Desperate-Organ-Transplants-Find-Black-Market" title="http://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20110512006179/en/Americans-Desperate-Organ-Transplants-Find-Black-Market">http://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20110512006179/en/Americans-Desper...</a>, accessed 20/08/11</p><p>Carney, Scott. “Why a Kidney (Street Value: $3,000) Sells for $85,000.” <em>Wired</em>. May 8, 2007. <a href="http://www.wired.com/medtech/health/news/2007/05/india_transplants_prices" title="http://www.wired.com/medtech/health/news/2007/05/india_transplants_prices">http://www.wired.com/medtech/health/news/2007/05/india_transplants_prices</a>, accessed 20/08/11.</p><p><em>Center for Human Reproduction. </em>http://www.centerforhumanreprod.com/, accessed 20/08/11.</p><p><em>Cleveland Clinic. </em>“Treatments &amp; Procedures: Lung Transplant.” <a href="http://my.clevelandclinic.org/services/lung_transplantation/hic_lung_transplant_your_commitment_to_good_health.aspx" title="http://my.clevelandclinic.org/services/lung_transplantation/hic_lung_transplant_your_commitment_to_good_health.aspx">http://my.clevelandclinic.org/services/lung_transplantation/hic_lung_tra...</a>, accessed 19/08/11.</p><p><em>Coalition to Investigate the Persecution of Falun Gong in China. </em>“Respected Surgeon Urges Others to Speak Out Against Forced Organ Donation in China.” <a href="http://cipfg.org/en/index.php?news=59" title="http://cipfg.org/en/index.php?news=59">http://cipfg.org/en/index.php?news=59</a>, accesed 20/08/11.</p><p><em>Comprehensive Transplant Center. </em>“Blood Type Incompatible Program.” <em>Johns Hopkins Medicine. </em>http://www.hopkinsmedicine.org/transplant/Programs/InKTP/blood_type.html, accessed 19/08/11.</p><p><em>Couple’s Guide to Jewish Fertility Challenges. </em>“Egg Donation.” <em>Puah Institute.</em> <a href="http://www.jewishfertility.org/egg-donation.php" title="http://www.jewishfertility.org/egg-donation.php">http://www.jewishfertility.org/egg-donation.php</a>, accessed 20/08/11.</p><p><em>Department of Health. </em>“Consent – what you have a right to expect.” <em>National Health Service. </em>http://www.dh.gov.uk/prod_consum_dh/groups/dh_digitalassets/@dh/@en/documents/digitalasset/dh_4066993.pdf, accessed 21/08/11.</p><p>Goodwin, Michele. “Confronting the Limits of Altruism: A Response to Jake Linford.” <em>Goodwin, vol. 2.</em> <a href="http://law.slu.edu/healthlaw/journal/archives/Goodwin.pdf" title="http://law.slu.edu/healthlaw/journal/archives/Goodwin.pdf">http://law.slu.edu/healthlaw/journal/archives/Goodwin.pdf</a>, accessed 20/08/11.</p><p>Guillen, Steve, <em>et al</em>. “Liver Transplant.” <em>eMedicine Health.</em> 2005, <a href="http://www.emedicinehealth.com/liver_transplant/article_em.htm" title="http://www.emedicinehealth.com/liver_transplant/article_em.htm">http://www.emedicinehealth.com/liver_transplant/article_em.htm</a>, accessed 20/08/11.</p><p><em>Havoscope: Black Markets</em>. “Kidney and Organ Prices.” <a href="http://www.havocscope.com/black-market-prices/organs-kidneys/" title="http://www.havocscope.com/black-market-prices/organs-kidneys/">http://www.havocscope.com/black-market-prices/organs-kidneys/</a>, accessed 19/08/11.</p><p><em>Imperial College of London. </em>“New study sets out to find why people don’t donate organs.” July 12, 2006. <a href="http://www1.imperial.ac.uk/medicine/news/donors/" title="http://www1.imperial.ac.uk/medicine/news/donors/">http://www1.imperial.ac.uk/medicine/news/donors/</a>, accessed 21/08/11.</p><p>Johnson, Eric J., and Daniel Goldstein, “Do Defaults Save Lives?”, <em>Science:</em> <em>Policy Forum</em>, Vol. 302, November 21, 2003, <a href="http://webs.wofford.edu/pechwj/Do%20Defaults%20Save%20Lives.pdf">http://webs.wofford.edu/pechwj/Do%20Defaults%20Save%20Lives.pdf</a>.</p><p><em>Kaycoff-Manos, Kathryn, and Lauri Berger de Brito. </em>“Overseas Egg Donation – The Good, the Bad and the Ugly.” <em>Parents via Egg Donation.</em> <a href="http://www.parentsviaeggdonation.org/v2/overseas_eggdonation.html" title="http://www.parentsviaeggdonation.org/v2/overseas_eggdonation.html">http://www.parentsviaeggdonation.org/v2/overseas_eggdonation.html</a>, accessed 20/08/11.</p><p>Kennedy, Louanne. “Health Policy and the Blood Market.” <em>Journal of Health Politics, Policy and Law.</em> 1978. <a href="http://jhppl.dukejournals.org/cgi/pdf_extract/3/1/5" title="http://jhppl.dukejournals.org/cgi/pdf_extract/3/1/5">http://jhppl.dukejournals.org/cgi/pdf_extract/3/1/5</a>, accessed 20/08/11.</p><p>Kram, Dena. “Illegal Human Organ Trade from Executed Prisoners in China.” <em>American University: TED Case Studies. </em>http://www1.american.edu/ted/prisonorgans.htm, accessed 19/08/11.</p><p>Lister, C.O. “Letter: Private medical care surely benefits NHS directly.” <em>BMJ.</em> <a href="http://www.bmj.com/content/319/7203/191.1.full" title="http://www.bmj.com/content/319/7203/191.1.full">http://www.bmj.com/content/319/7203/191.1.full</a>, accessed 20/08/11.</p><p>MacKinnon, Paula. “Black market in organs uncovered.” <em>BBC. </em>July 9, 2008. <a href="http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/scotland/7493466.stm" title="http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/scotland/7493466.stm">http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/scotland/7493466.stm</a>, accessed 19/08/11.</p><p><em>Narconon. </em>“Illegal Drugs.” <a href="http://www.drugrehab.co.uk/illegal-drugs.htm" title="http://www.drugrehab.co.uk/illegal-drugs.htm">http://www.drugrehab.co.uk/illegal-drugs.htm</a>, accessed 20/08/11.</p><p><em>On a quiet day, I can hear her breathing [blog]</em>. “NHS news review.” July 29, 2011. <a href="http://www.onaquietday.org/2011/07/29/nhs-news-review-94/" title="http://www.onaquietday.org/2011/07/29/nhs-news-review-94/">http://www.onaquietday.org/2011/07/29/nhs-news-review-94/</a>, accessed 20/08/11.</p><p><em>Science Daily. </em>“Donor Race May Impact Kidney Transplant Survival.”&nbsp; October 31, 2009. <a href="http://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2009/10/091030125042.htm" title="http://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2009/10/091030125042.htm">http://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2009/10/091030125042.htm</a>, accessed 21/08/11.</p><p><em>Sperm Bank, Inc. </em>“Purchase Donor Sperm.” <em>Fertility Center of California. </em>http://www.spermbankcalifornia.com/buy-sperm-online.html, accessed 20/08/11.</p><p>Suddath, Claire and Alex Altman. “How Does Kidney-Trafficking Work?” <em>Time Magazine.</em> July 27, 2009. <a href="http://www.time.com/time/health/article/0,8599,1912880,00.html" title="http://www.time.com/time/health/article/0,8599,1912880,00.html">http://www.time.com/time/health/article/0,8599,1912880,00.html</a>, accessed 20/08/11.</p><p><em>Surrogate Mothers, Inc. </em>http://www.surrogatemothers.com/, accessed 20/08/11.</p><p><em>United Network for Organ Sharing. </em>http://www.unos.org/ accessed 19/08/11.</p><p><em>U.S. Drug Enforcement Administration. </em>“Drug Classes.” <a href="http://www.justice.gov/dea/concern/dextroproxyphene.html#drugclasses" title="http://www.justice.gov/dea/concern/dextroproxyphene.html#drugclasses">http://www.justice.gov/dea/concern/dextroproxyphene.html#drugclasses</a>, accessed 20/08/11.</p><p>Wheeler, Robert. “Consent in Surgery.” <em>The Annals of the Royal College of Surgeons of England. </em>May 2006. <a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC1963696/" title="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC1963696/">http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC1963696/</a>, accessed 21/08/11.</p><p>Woodcock, Sue. “Body parts and the law.” <em>Nursing Times. </em>February 8, 2001. Vol 96, issue 06. <a href="http://www.nursingtimes.net/nursing-practice-clinical-research/body-parts-and-the-law/206118.article" title="http://www.nursingtimes.net/nursing-practice-clinical-research/body-parts-and-the-law/206118.article">http://www.nursingtimes.net/nursing-practice-clinical-research/body-part...</a>, accessed 21/08/11.</p>    </div>
    
